   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Following the consulate of the viri clarissimi, Flavius Probus and Flavius Abienus, on the 12th of Phamenoth of the 11th indiction, in Arsinoe.  Aurelius Pamun, son of Aion, a farmer from the city of the Arsinoites, from the district of Ecclesia Kainon, to Aurelius Heracleides, son of (name omitted), also a farmer from the same city, greetings.  I acknowledge personally to have received from you for my own necessary use half a gold solidus, as principal in accordance with convention, and to have received in full the price of 3 1/2 artabs of wheat of highest quality.</ab>
